name: Tom Cruise
summary: Tom Cruise was the star of the Paris Olympics closing ceremony, performing a daredevil stunt that involved leaping from the stadium's roof and skydiving to the ground. This audacious move signaled the transition of Olympic hosting duties to Los Angeles. Despite speculation surrounding his rumored relationship with 25-year-old Victoria Canal, Canal has denied the claims, indicating a significant age gap between them. Cruise's Olympics stunt has garnered widespread praise for its adrenaline-pumping spectacle, cementing his status as an action star.

name: LeBron James
summary: LeBron James, now 39, continues to lead the US basketball team in the 2024 Olympics, motivated by his family and aiming for another gold medal. Despite being in his likely final Olympic Games, James is enjoying the experience and inspiring his team. Under the guidance of coach Steve Kerr, the US team defeated Brazil to reach the semifinals. While it is unlikely that James or Stephen Curry will compete in the 2028 Olympics, Kevin Durant remains open to the possibility. Speculation has arisen linking James to a potential reunion with the Miami Heat following comments from Jimmy Butler. James' pursuit of a third Olympic gold medal has drawn attention, with Team USA cherishing his presence. Additionally, James' facial injury during the Olympics has led to him receiving stitches.

name: Sifan Hassan
summary: Sifan Hassan achieved an unprecedented feat at the Paris Olympics, becoming the first athlete to win three medals in distance running at a single Games. She secured gold in the women's marathon, adding to her bronze in the 5,000 meters and silver in the 10,000 meters. Hassan's triumph in the marathon was particularly remarkable, as she engaged in a thrilling sprint finish with Tigst Assefa, showcasing her exceptional endurance. The Dutch runner's Olympic treble has been hailed as one of the greatest achievements in the history of the Summer Games, cementing her status as a legendary distance runner.

name: Winter Olympics
summary: The 2024 Paris Games are nearing their conclusion, prompting attention to shift towards the upcoming 2026 Milan Cortina Winter Olympics. The 2026 Games will be held in Milan and Cortina d'Ampezzo, Italy. Beijing Winter Olympics medals have been reallocated in Paris, with the Japanese figure skating team receiving a celebration from Paris 2024 organizers. The 2028 Summer Olympics will be held in Los Angeles, California. The 2034 Winter Olympics are scheduled for Salt Lake City, Utah, with a termination clause included in the contract. The 2026 Olympics will take place from February 6th to 22nd, 2026, featuring the logo of a stylized snowflake. Additional information about these future Olympic Games is available for further exploration.

name: Jordan Chiles
summary: After a lengthy legal battle, Romanian gymnast Catalina Ponor is poised to reclaim the bronze medal in floor exercise from American gymnast Jordan Chiles. The International Olympic Committee (IOC) ruled that Ponor's original score should have been upheld, while Chiles' score was incorrectly elevated. Chiles must now surrender her bronze medal. Despite this setback, Chiles remains eligible to compete in the upcoming 2025 season with UCLA Athletics.
